[[File:Humidify icon (mobile).png|left]]
The '''humidify''' spell will fill all empty water-carrying vessels in a player's inventory with a single cast including: [[bucket]]s, [[fishbowl]]s, [[jug]]s, [[vial]]s, [[watering can]]s (including [[Gricoller's can]]), unwatered [[sapling]]s, [[waterskin]]s, [[bowl]]s, and [[clay]].
Somewhat surprisingly, it does '''not''' work on [[Empty cup]]s. It yields 65 [[experience]] per cast regardless of the number of vessels filled. It can also be used to extinguish the wall of flames in the [[Chambers of Xeric]] when fighting [[Great Olm]] or to refill waterskins in the [[Kharidian Desert]] instead of needing to cut [[Kharidian cactus|cacti]]. 

A [[steam battlestaff]], or [[staff of water]] and [[tome of fire]] or [[staff of fire|vice]] [[tome of water|versa]] can be used for maximum efficiency. It can be used to train [[Magic]] while making profit from some of the items below:
